 France Breaking NewsKim Jong Un vows to ‘hold hands’ with Russia’s Putin for strategic cooperation Breaking NewsAfzaal family remembered on second anniversary of the Islamophobic attack in London Breaking NewsGermany Defence Ministry concerned over ex-pilots sharing secrets with ChinaRealestate AllBollywoodMovie ReviewsSoap MasalaSports Bollywood‘I love you so much’: Selena Gomez admits she is ‘single’ during soccer BollywoodWhen Sonam Kapoor revealed why she married Anand Ahuja: He saw the person in me and not some glamorous heroine BollywoodTiger Shroff’s mom Ayesha Shroff cheated of ₹58 lakh, files police case BollywoodOMG 2: Akshay Kumar looks unrecognisable as Shiva with dreadlocks, announces release date; film to clash with Gadar 2 BollywoodKangana Ranaut bids goodbye to airport looks after ‘starting the trend’, says she ‘was brainwashed by fashion industry’EntertainmentPunjab Link  Breaking NewsPunjabi become fastest-growing language in various countries of the world Breaking Newsਕੋਵਿਡ-19 ਨੇ ਵਧਾਇਆ ਤਣਾਅ ! ਪ੍ਰਧਾਨ ਮੰਤਰੀ ਮੋਦੀ ਅੱਜ ਕਰਨਗੇ ਉੱਚ ਪੱਧਰੀ ਮੀਟਿੰਗ, ਦੇਸ਼ ‘ਚ ਕੋਰੋਨਾ ਦੀ ਸਥਿਤੀ ‘ਤੇ ਹੋਵੇਗੀ ਚਰਚਾ Breaking Newsਕੋਰੋਨਾ ਨੂੰ ਲੈ ਕੇ ਇੰਡੀਅਨ ਮੈਡੀਕਲ ਐਸੋਸੀਏਸ਼ਨ ਦੀ ਲੋਕਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਚਿਤਾਵਨੀ, ਪ੍ਰੋਟੋਕੋਲ ਨਾ ਮੰਨਿਆ ਤਾਂ… Breaking NewsPunjab CM Bhagwant Mann ties the knot with Haryana doctor Gurpreet Kaur Breaking NewsIn Punjab today, CM weds doctor; Arvind Kejriwal among few inviteesNews AllAuto LinkBusinessFiji NewsHealthLead StoryLink NewsSouth AsianTop News Breaking NewsObituary: Sardarni Dalip Kaur Hundal Breaking NewsVancouver based South Asian lawyer launches book to teach kids gratitude Breaking NewsTwo arrested in homicide of Surinderjit Singh Breaking NewsBC to send Cancer patients to Bellingham clinics for radiation treatment Breaking NewsUnsafe conditions at Surrey Memorial Hospital “compel” emergency physicians to write open letter to publicCalender  Breaking NewsBurnaby RCMP Seize Large Amount Of Drugand Weapons Near Elementary School And Daycare Breaking NewsCFIB urges municipal policymakers to keep costs down for local businesses CalenderGoogle IT Support Certificate Program Info Sessions CalenderCalendar of Week CalenderCalendar of the WeekSouth Asian  Breaking NewsSouth Asian Philanthropists join hands for Cancer Fundraiser Breaking NewsHelp locate high risk missing South Asian male BalharKandola Breaking NewsIHIT appeal to public on two-year anniversary of Trina Hunt investigation Breaking NewsIndia restores e-Visa services for Canadian Passport holders Breaking NewsAruna Miller makes history as first South Asian woman elected lieutenant governor in U.S.SearchHome  Breaking News  Meninder Dhaliwal, Satindera Gill shot dead in brazen daylight gang related shooting...Breaking NewscanadaMeninder Dhaliwal, Satindera Gill shot dead in brazen daylight gang related shooting in Whistler, Gursimran Sahota and Tanvir Khakh of Surrey chargedBy Team Link - July 30, 20220289Facebook Twitter Pinterest WhatsApp  SURREY: The sound of Lower Mainland gang war was heard in mountains last Sunday which rocked the idyllic mountain ski community of Whistler. In another brazen daylight shooting two South Asian male members were shot at the Sundial Boutique Hotel, located in the 4300 block of Sundial Crescent, Whistler, B.C. on July 24th.The police later identified the victims of shooting as Satindera Gill and Meninder Dhaliwal who according to IHTI, “were both known to police.” “This is believed to have been a targeted shooting, in relation to the ongoing Lower Mainland gang conflict,” informed Sergeant Timothy Pierotti of IHIT.According to various media reports Meninder Dhaliwal was “Brothers Keepers” gang member. Dhaliwal’s younger brother Harb was shot in Vancouver’s Coal Harbour area last year in a targeted hit. In 2021, Meninder Dhaliwal’s name was on the list of VPD’s top 6 gangsters with links to Vancouver “who posed a significant risk to the safety of the public.”Video of the gruesome aftermath went viral that showed Dhaliwal, wearing a white T-shirt and shorts and an over the shoulder satchel, face down in the hotel parking lot, in a pool of blood.Gill was seen splayed out on the other side of a parked white BMW where a bystander appears to be trying to aid him, the video shows.Dhaliwal died at the scene and Gill was rushed to an area hospital where he succumbed to his gunshot wounds.The community around Whistler Mountain, home of the 2010 Winter Olympics, was temporarily locked down by the RCMP. However police declared the area risk free later. “I’m confident with the work done by our investigators that there remains no risk to community safety,” said Inspector Robert Dykstra, Officer in Charge of the Sea to Sky RCMP.One victim died on scene, while the other died as a result of injuries, a short time later after being transported to hospital.A burning vehicle believed to be associated to the shooting was located in the 3300 block of Ptarmigan Place, in Whistler, B.C.Sea-to-Sky RCMP were able to locate and apprehend multiple individuals. The Integrated Homicide Investigation Team (IHIT) took conduct of the investigation and in partnership with the Sea-to-Sky Whistler RCMP.On July 25, 2022, following a consultation with BC Prosecution Service, charges of first-degree murder were approved against 24-year-old Gursimran Sahota, from Surrey and 20-year-old Tanvir Khakh, from Surrey.“This act was outrageous and shock to the visitors and community of Whistler,” said Sergeant David Lee of IHIT, “these results are thanks to the real-time information provided and the quick actions of the First Responders.”Three other individuals were arrested along with Khakh and Sahota. The extent of their involvement is still being determined. This investigation is still ongoing.Anyone with information is asked to contact the IHIT Information Line at 1-877-551-IHIT (4448) or by email at [email protected].Facebook Twitter Pinterest WhatsApp  Previous article2 young men arrested and charged in shooting of Ripudaman Singh MalikNext articl